WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.180
Missing children has become an epidemic for our people.

2
00:00:03.263 --> 00:00:04.719
Mom reported her missing four months ago.

3
00:00:04.803 --> 00:00:06.093
Could be a victim of trafficking.

4
00:00:06.177 --> 00:00:07.758
Hayley. give me something. okay?

5
00:00:07.841 --> 00:00:09.173
You got to help me find you guys.

6
00:00:09.256 --> 00:00:10.213
Another stop they take us to.

7
00:00:10.297 --> 00:00:11.254
The place with the trees. Get us there.

8
00:00:11.337 --> 00:00:13.127
- What about... - You have to let me go.

9
00:00:13.210 --> 00:00:15.374
Hayley falls right into our hands and Kayce tosses her back

10
00:00:15.457 --> 00:00:16.790
- to a killer. - The place

11
00:00:16.873 --> 00:00:18.621
with the trees isn't about actual trees.

12
00:00:18.704 --> 00:00:19.662
It's a logo.

13
00:00:19.745 --> 00:00:21.326
Camper's how Bludsoe's moving them.

14
00:00:22.242 --> 00:00:23.907
They're gone.

15
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:31.074
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.com ] ==-

16
00:01:23.715 --> 00:01:26.212
Why are you pumping lead this early?

17
00:01:26.295 --> 00:01:28.209
Just clearing my head.

18
00:01:28.292 --> 00:01:30.123
So. no news on Hayley?

19
00:01:35.202 --> 00:01:36.950
So much for honoring Mom by finding her.

20
00:02:00.798 --> 00:02:04.127
I'm guessing those combos means there's nothing new

21
00:02:04.210 --> 00:02:06.541
- about the missing girls. huh?

22
00:02:06.624 --> 00:02:09.913
Kurt Bludsoe and his scumbag henchmen are still dead.

23
00:02:09.995 --> 00:02:11.327
and the FBI is still slow-walking

24
00:02:11.411 --> 00:02:13.284
information requests.

25
00:02:13.367 --> 00:02:15.531
Two days of round-the-clock work

26
00:02:15.614 --> 00:02:17.862
and no new actionables.

27
00:02:19.693 --> 00:02:21.815
Hey. I've let you stall long enough.

28
00:02:21.899 --> 00:02:24.187
Okay? You have to do Ava's next-of-kin notification today.

29
00:02:24.271 --> 00:02:25.728
no matter what.

30
00:02:25.811 --> 00:02:27.309
Finding the girls is my priority.

31
00:02:27.393 --> 00:02:29.141
Why rush the worst day of her mom's life?

32
00:02:29.224 --> 00:02:32.637
Because Sera deserves to know the truth. Miles.

33
00:02:32.720 --> 00:02:36.216
so giving her a shot at closure is your new priority.

34
00:02:36.299 --> 00:02:38.214
Maybe Kayce should tell her.

35
00:02:38.297 --> 00:02:40.628
Then he can swing by Hayley's mom's after.

36
00:02:40.711 --> 00:02:42.584
share how he let her daughter go.

37
00:02:46.746 --> 00:02:48.785
It's just his emotions talking.

38
00:02:49.826 --> 00:02:51.366
Got an update.

39
00:02:51.449 --> 00:02:54.612
Bludsoe visited a mechanic shop shortly before we killed him.

40
00:02:54.695 --> 00:02:56.360
Thinking that's where he ditched the girls?

41
00:02:56.443 --> 00:02:57.941
Maybe. He called the mechanic

42
00:02:58.024 --> 00:03:00.022
on his cell. Eli Craig.

43
00:03:00.106 --> 00:03:04.434
Uh. the guy's got no sheet. but it's worth pursuing.

44
00:03:04.517 --> 00:03:05.850
Put thousands of miles on that camper

45
00:03:05.932 --> 00:03:08.929
crossing the region. you know. it stands to reason

46
00:03:09.012 --> 00:03:10.469
that he'd need a tune-up every now and then.

47
00:03:10.552 --> 00:03:11.926
Better than anything we've got.

48
00:03:12.009 --> 00:03:14.298
Mm. Well. Miles and I are doing the notification today.

49
00:03:14.381 --> 00:03:16.463
so the rest of y'all. dig into the connections

50
00:03:16.546 --> 00:03:19.709
between Bludsoe and this mechanic Craig.

51
00:03:19.792 --> 00:03:21.707
We should figure out who the other nine girls are.

52
00:03:21.790 --> 00:03:23.580
Get their faces out there. see if someone spots one.

53
00:03:23.663 --> 00:03:25.618
- On it. - Only works

54
00:03:25.702 --> 00:03:27.908
if they call it in instead of letting them go.

55
00:04:06.073 --> 00:04:07.821
Ava's mother is at work. so...

56
00:04:07.905 --> 00:04:10.568
we're gonna do the notification there.

57
00:04:10.652 --> 00:04:13.190
Great. At Rainwater's office.

58
00:04:13.274 --> 00:04:15.437
Should be hunting for the girls rather than flaunting my failure

59
00:04:15.521 --> 00:04:16.853
to the chairman.

60
00:04:16.936 --> 00:04:18.476
Can't blame yourself for a fight

61
00:04:18.559 --> 00:04:20.556
that even Rainwater said he can't take on.

62
00:04:20.640 --> 00:04:23.303
People of Broken Rock deserve better.

63
00:04:23.387 --> 00:04:25.718
And Ava's mother deserves hearing the worst

64
00:04:25.801 --> 00:04:27.882
from someone who cares.

65
00:04:27.965 --> 00:04:30.920
And as painful as that is for you. Miles...

66
00:04:32.418 --> 00:04:34.291
...that's why you need to be there.

67
00:04:36.164 --> 00:04:37.871
You done these before?

68
00:04:40.326 --> 00:04:43.198
Yeah. some for men who died 'cause of calls I made.

69
00:04:45.321 --> 00:04:47.193
That's got to be rough.

70
00:04:48.400 --> 00:04:49.608
You know...

71
00:04:51.022 --> 00:04:54.103
...I took the Angel Flight with the first teammate I lost.

72
00:04:54.186 --> 00:04:56.725
And the XO of the team and I. we-we made the notification

73
00:04:56.808 --> 00:04:58.805
to his wife and his kid.

74
00:04:59.804 --> 00:05:01.220
And. uh...

75
00:05:03.051 --> 00:05:05.048
...I couldn't even get a word out.

76
00:05:06.505 --> 00:05:08.045
And afterwards. that XO.

77
00:05:08.128 --> 00:05:10.210
he pulled me aside and he said to me.

78
00:05:10.292 --> 00:05:14.246
"We do this job because others can't."

79
00:05:17.867 --> 00:05:19.782
Bludsoe spent less time at the mechanic

80
00:05:19.865 --> 00:05:22.362
than he did at any of the truck stops he visited.

81
00:05:22.446 --> 00:05:25.318
Safe to assume he wasn't there pimping the girls.

82
00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:27.440
He had to have dropped them somewhere.

83
00:05:27.523 --> 00:05:29.853
and this is the last point of contact

84
00:05:29.937 --> 00:05:31.685
before we caught up with Bludsoe.

85
00:05:31.768 --> 00:05:36.138
So. Craig is the next link in the trafficking chain?

86
00:05:36.221 --> 00:05:38.428
We bring him in for questioning. my interrogation's a lot easier

87
00:05:38.511 --> 00:05:40.426
if I already have most of the answers.

88
00:05:42.964 --> 00:05:46.627
Parking lot across the street has security cameras.

89
00:05:46.709 --> 00:05:49.373
Bet you one is aimed at the shop.

90
00:05:55.949 --> 00:06:00.069
Receptionist called. saying U.S. Marshals were here.

91
00:06:00.153 --> 00:06:02.151
And I said that couldn't be true.

92
00:06:02.234 --> 00:06:05.647
because I'm certain I would be their first call

93
00:06:05.730 --> 00:06:09.726
if they had any information about our missing girls.

94
00:06:09.808 --> 00:06:11.931
Well. that's my mistake. sir.

95
00:06:12.015 --> 00:06:13.264
I thought it was appropriate

96
00:06:13.346 --> 00:06:15.344
to speak with Ava's mother first.

97
00:06:16.385 --> 00:06:17.467
Speak with her?

98
00:06:18.591 --> 00:06:19.839
About what?

99
00:06:29.536 --> 00:06:31.368
I see.

100
00:06:32.700 --> 00:06:35.072
My worst fears have come true once again.

101
00:06:36.487 --> 00:06:38.401
Tragedy is one of the few things

102
00:06:38.485 --> 00:06:41.190
Broken Rock has in abundance.

103
00:06:42.356 --> 00:06:44.686
How did you learn of Ava's fate?

104
00:06:44.769 --> 00:06:47.308
Hayley. She told Kayce.

105
00:06:47.391 --> 00:06:48.765
Right before he let her go.

106
00:06:51.137 --> 00:06:53.718
Uh. Hayley. though. made it clear. sir. that...

107
00:06:54.717 --> 00:06:57.297
...if she had left. other girls would've been killed.

108
00:06:57.380 --> 00:06:59.627
- And so. Kayce

109
00:06:59.711 --> 00:07:03.041
took that risk in order to protect the rest of the group.

110
00:07:03.123 --> 00:07:06.329
And how can he protect them when you can't find them?

111
00:07:11.323 --> 00:07:12.697
Forty-three girls have been

112
00:07:12.780 --> 00:07:15.069
reported missing from reservations in Montana

113
00:07:15.152 --> 00:07:16.858
over the past two years.

114
00:07:16.942 --> 00:07:18.690
Forty-three?

115
00:07:18.773 --> 00:07:21.894
Fourteen had contact with your guy Greeneyes44.

116
00:07:21.977 --> 00:07:25.099
Doing my best to identify the other predators.

117
00:07:26.764 --> 00:07:29.386
Forty-three doesn't even seem possible.

118
00:07:29.469 --> 00:07:31.675
And those are just the ones reported.

119
00:07:47.408 --> 00:07:51.319
Miles. I didn't expect to see you again so soon.

120
00:07:52.402 --> 00:07:55.523
Was Ava's social media information useful?

121
00:07:59.394 --> 00:08:01.308
Uh...

122
00:08:01.392 --> 00:08:03.348
- Thing is. ma'am. um... - Ma'am?

123
00:08:04.014 --> 00:08:05.470
You've called me "Auntie" since you were in diapers.

124
00:08:12.504 --> 00:08:14.752
Miles. what's going on?

125
00:08:20.121 --> 00:08:24.074
Uh. ma'am. uh...

126
00:08:24.157 --> 00:08:25.697
I mean. Auntie.

127
00:08:25.780 --> 00:08:27.196
it's. um...

128
00:08:27.279 --> 00:08:29.318
It's not. uh...

129
00:08:29.401 --> 00:08:30.817
What happened?

130
00:08:33.564 --> 00:08:35.853
I am so sorry. ma'am.

131
00:08:35.936 --> 00:08:38.391
but Ava's no longer with us.

132
00:08:38.475 --> 00:08:40.473
She was killed by the men trafficking her.

133
00:08:44.509 --> 00:08:45.800
No.

134
00:08:47.756 --> 00:08:49.171
Please.

135
00:08:50.212 --> 00:08:51.751
Please.

136
00:08:55.706 --> 00:08:56.995
Please.

137
00:08:58.827 --> 00:09:00.866
Ava's on a better journey now.

138
00:09:00.950 --> 00:09:02.948
No. Ava.

139
00:09:03.030 --> 00:09:05.195
My deepest condolences.

140
00:09:05.278 --> 00:09:07.401
My baby...

141
00:09:13.311 --> 00:09:14.934
There's Bludsoe.

142
00:09:16.682 --> 00:09:18.346
That could be Craig.

143
00:09:18.430 --> 00:09:20.386
Okay. so. Bludsoe's timeline has him there

144
00:09:20.469 --> 00:09:24.298
at 3:48 p.m. two days ago.

145
00:09:24.381 --> 00:09:27.545
He's there for eight minutes until...

146
00:09:30.500 --> 00:09:32.040
Who the hell is this?

147
00:09:32.123 --> 00:09:33.663
What is this. some sort of meet?

148
00:09:33.746 --> 00:09:36.243
How long are they in there?

149
00:09:36.326 --> 00:09:37.658
Less than five minutes.

150
00:09:43.942 --> 00:09:46.065
Uh. can you zoom in?

151
00:09:52.142 --> 00:09:54.265
That's an Iron Sentinels vest.

152
00:09:54.348 --> 00:09:56.678
The girls are in the hands of a violent motorcycle gang.

153
00:10:05.085 --> 00:10:06.708
Wheatland County deputies detained Eli Craig for us.

154
00:10:06.791 --> 00:10:08.373
but he has lawyered up and not talking.

155
00:10:08.456 --> 00:10:09.912
Uh. so best-case scenario.

156
00:10:09.996 --> 00:10:11.744
the girls are being run by an outlaw biker gang.

157
00:10:11.827 --> 00:10:14.282
Iron Sentinels are a true one-percenter gang.

158
00:10:14.366 --> 00:10:17.238
They're ultraviolent and highly organized.

159
00:10:17.321 --> 00:10:18.944
Any ties to sex trafficking?

160
00:10:19.027 --> 00:10:21.025
Drugs and weapons are their big operation.

161
00:10:21.109 --> 00:10:22.857
but they're a mafia on wheels.

162
00:10:22.939 --> 00:10:27.102
If they can profit from it. they'll do it.

163
00:10:27.185 --> 00:10:28.850
They've got a clubhouse out by Cowan.

164
00:10:28.933 --> 00:10:31.180
Place is a full-on biker bar.

165
00:10:31.263 --> 00:10:34.468
Always busy. heavily fortified.

166
00:10:34.551 --> 00:10:36.133
Not a door you want to kick.

167
00:10:49.452 --> 00:10:51.532
Okay. Let's get surveillance up.

168
00:10:51.615 --> 00:10:53.238
see if we can get eyes on these girls.

169
00:10:57.401 --> 00:10:59.398
How'd it go with Ava's mom?

170
00:11:05.392 --> 00:11:08.221
You walk out of a notification thinking it went well...

171
00:11:09.470 --> 00:11:11.093
...didn't do it right.

172
00:11:14.424 --> 00:11:15.713
I choked.

173
00:11:16.712 --> 00:11:17.628
My dad's partner

174
00:11:17.711 --> 00:11:19.958
notified our family after he was killed.

175
00:11:20.957 --> 00:11:23.247
Just doing his job. but...

176
00:11:23.329 --> 00:11:25.827
I hated him for it.

177
00:11:25.911 --> 00:11:27.367
Tore him a new one.

178
00:11:27.450 --> 00:11:29.572
That's hard to imagine.

179
00:11:34.234 --> 00:11:36.524
I didn't cry at my dad's funeral.

180
00:11:38.896 --> 00:11:41.726
I was too overwhelmed by the loss to actually grieve.

181
00:11:42.725 --> 00:11:45.097
Tears can't fix a hole in your heart.

182
00:11:45.180 --> 00:11:47.594
Maybe not. but...

183
00:11:48.843 --> 00:11:52.256
...that flat. hollow feeling

184
00:11:52.339 --> 00:11:54.087
kept spreading.

185
00:11:54.170 --> 00:11:57.416
until I acknowledged my grief

186
00:11:57.500 --> 00:11:59.331
and gave it a shape.

187
00:11:59.414 --> 00:12:00.829
What the hell kind of shape are you supposed to give

188
00:12:00.912 --> 00:12:02.286
that kind of pain?

189
00:12:02.370 --> 00:12:05.491
Any kind. as long as you control it

190
00:12:05.574 --> 00:12:07.697
instead of the other way around.

191
00:12:08.737 --> 00:12:11.359
Maybe you hold it gently.

192
00:12:12.358 --> 00:12:14.564
Maybe you walk through it and find closure.

193
00:12:17.436 --> 00:12:19.641
It's different for everyone.

194
00:12:23.761 --> 00:12:25.385
This isn't working.

195
00:12:26.384 --> 00:12:29.255
If we can't go in. maybe we can drive them out.

196
00:12:29.339 --> 00:12:31.212
You want to pull a fire alarm?

197
00:12:31.295 --> 00:12:33.210
Call in a bomb threat?

198
00:12:33.293 --> 00:12:35.623
How are you gonna force them out of their sanctuary?

199
00:12:38.370 --> 00:12:40.118
By going after what they love.

200
00:13:18.866 --> 00:13:21.613
Clubhouse is clearing out. Go.

201
00:13:32.726 --> 00:13:34.016
The girls aren't here.

202
00:13:38.012 --> 00:13:39.385
They're heading back in.

203
00:13:49.415 --> 00:13:50.748
All right. you're clear.

204
00:13:50.830 --> 00:13:52.246
Grab whatever intel you can.

205
00:14:09.476 --> 00:14:10.683
We got to move. Come on.

206
00:14:10.766 --> 00:14:11.974
Done.

207
00:14:14.721 --> 00:14:16.718
Cell phone we ripped suggests the girls could be

208
00:14:16.801 --> 00:14:17.925
at an Iron Sentinels rally

209
00:14:18.008 --> 00:14:19.631
happening up at the Milk River valley area.

210
00:14:19.715 --> 00:14:21.629
And that rally will bring in chapters

211
00:14:21.713 --> 00:14:23.252
from around the country.

212
00:14:23.336 --> 00:14:25.458
Bikers going off into the wild getting weird

213
00:14:25.541 --> 00:14:27.165
could mean a demand for girls.

214
00:14:27.247 --> 00:14:29.037
I pulled a text from the cell phone we ripped.

215
00:14:29.120 --> 00:14:31.243
Says. "Brimstone's bringing the entertainment."

216
00:14:31.951 --> 00:14:33.699
Entertainment?

217
00:14:33.782 --> 00:14:35.447
That could be drugs. y'all.

218
00:14:35.530 --> 00:14:37.985
And Bludsoe could've dumped them elsewhere for all we know.

219
00:14:38.069 --> 00:14:39.276
Right?

220
00:14:40.317 --> 00:14:41.565
It's the girls.

221
00:14:42.605 --> 00:14:44.603
Yeah. who's this "Brimstone"?

222
00:14:44.687 --> 00:14:48.474
Uh. Keith Stelton. an Iron Sentinel nomad.

223
00:14:48.557 --> 00:14:52.136
Nomads are the most feared members of the biker gangs.

224
00:14:52.219 --> 00:14:54.384
They don't have a home chapter. and are a combination

225
00:14:54.467 --> 00:14:57.298
of the club's fixers and enforcers.

226
00:14:57.381 --> 00:14:59.711
Deserved rep based off of Brimstone's sheet.

227
00:14:59.795 --> 00:15:01.833
Assault. battery. armed robbery.

228
00:15:01.917 --> 00:15:03.831
and he's been investigated for weapons

229
00:15:03.915 --> 00:15:05.496
and narcotics distribution.

230
00:15:05.579 --> 00:15:06.828
He's a guy who can move things.

231
00:15:06.912 --> 00:15:07.952
Yeah. but can you link him

232
00:15:08.036 --> 00:15:09.117
to whatever went down at the mechanic's?

233
00:15:09.200 --> 00:15:11.073
Texts indicate he arrived

234
00:15:11.157 --> 00:15:13.321
an hour before the van visited Craig's garage.

235
00:15:13.404 --> 00:15:15.069
Connection to the girls is still thin. Dre.

236
00:15:15.152 --> 00:15:16.817
Okay? And I got Gifford

237
00:15:16.901 --> 00:15:19.106
up my ass for spending so much time on this. y'all.

238
00:15:19.189 --> 00:15:20.687
Well. then. he'll be happy to know that if the girls

239
00:15:20.771 --> 00:15:23.684
aren't at the rally. the trail will have run cold.

240
00:15:31.217 --> 00:15:32.758
Okay. Reach out to state and local police.

241
00:15:32.841 --> 00:15:34.713
see if we can plus up our forces. Hey.

242
00:15:34.796 --> 00:15:38.834
And if we can get the support. then we'll hit the rally.

243
00:16:11.007 --> 00:16:12.755
What's going on?

244
00:16:12.838 --> 00:16:14.044
Forgive the imposition.

245
00:16:15.210 --> 00:16:16.833
Tate was expecting us.

246
00:16:17.832 --> 00:16:20.746
Came to help him to prepare for the ceremony.

247
00:16:20.829 --> 00:16:22.369
but his horse is gone.

248
00:16:22.452 --> 00:16:25.448
Are you taking a break from the investigation?

249
00:16:25.531 --> 00:16:28.653
'Cause time must be running low.

250
00:16:28.737 --> 00:16:30.651
as are our hopes.

251
00:16:30.734 --> 00:16:33.023
I came home to check on my son.

252
00:16:34.022 --> 00:16:35.645
Hayley news hit him pretty hard.

253
00:16:35.729 --> 00:16:37.851
Timing can't be easy on him.

254
00:16:37.934 --> 00:16:39.765
marking a year without a mother.

255
00:16:39.849 --> 00:16:42.221
a friend taken by wolves.

256
00:16:42.304 --> 00:16:45.259
And a father who returned her to the very same pack.

257
00:16:45.343 --> 00:16:47.590
Did you come here to beat me up?

258
00:16:47.673 --> 00:16:49.588
'Cause I've been doing plenty of that myself.

259
00:16:49.671 --> 00:16:51.211
Well. from what Mo tells me.

260
00:16:51.294 --> 00:16:53.250
you've been punishing more than yourself.

261
00:16:55.747 --> 00:16:59.410
Listen. retribution is a form of justice.

262
00:17:00.409 --> 00:17:03.114
But don't confuse vengeance with closure.

263
00:17:03.198 --> 00:17:04.737
Only one brings peace.

264
00:17:04.821 --> 00:17:07.359
Well. vengeance is the one I believe in.

265
00:17:07.443 --> 00:17:09.482
The tighter we cling to our grief.

266
00:17:09.566 --> 00:17:12.937
the bigger shadow our sorrow casts behind us.

267
00:17:14.019 --> 00:17:15.767
Finding our girls

268
00:17:15.850 --> 00:17:20.553
is the type of closure that even you can believe in. Kayce.

269
00:17:36.493 --> 00:17:39.407
Once you bring us this peace.

270
00:17:39.490 --> 00:17:41.155
and if you find the pack of wolves

271
00:17:41.238 --> 00:17:42.903
preying on our children...

272
00:17:43.985 --> 00:17:45.900
...slaughter them all.

273
00:17:56.054 --> 00:17:57.595
Okay. where are we with federal assets?

274
00:17:57.678 --> 00:18:00.217
Same place as our local assets: nowhere.

275
00:18:00.300 --> 00:18:01.923
They either don't have the resources

276
00:18:02.007 --> 00:18:03.338
or they won't allocate them.

277
00:18:03.421 --> 00:18:05.294
I'm starting to feel Chairman Rainwater's pain.

278
00:18:05.378 --> 00:18:06.917
So. if we make any moves on this biker rally.

279
00:18:07.001 --> 00:18:08.333
we'll be operating solo.

280
00:18:08.415 --> 00:18:10.330
No. We cannot pull off direct action

281
00:18:10.413 --> 00:18:12.245
on this rally with only five shooters.

282
00:18:12.328 --> 00:18:14.076
But we get eyes and ears inside the rally.

283
00:18:14.159 --> 00:18:15.283
locate the girls.

284
00:18:15.367 --> 00:18:17.489
may help convince the other agencies to spin up.

285
00:18:17.572 --> 00:18:19.153
plus up our manpower.

286
00:18:19.237 --> 00:18:20.943
It's a members-only rally. okay?

287
00:18:21.026 --> 00:18:22.983
We get caught poking around with this crew.

288
00:18:23.066 --> 00:18:24.856
and we're gonna be in a hurt locker.

289
00:18:24.939 --> 00:18:27.269
A marshal would stand out. but a biker wouldn't.

290
00:18:27.353 --> 00:18:29.267
Okay.

291
00:18:29.351 --> 00:18:31.848
You mind telling me what the hell you're getting at?

292
00:18:33.138 --> 00:18:34.261
I ran an undercover sting

293
00:18:34.345 --> 00:18:36.509
against the Iron Sentinels a few years back.

294
00:18:36.593 --> 00:18:39.672
My mark was a member of the St. Louis chapter.

295
00:18:39.755 --> 00:18:40.921
Yeah. I heard about that op.

296
00:18:41.004 --> 00:18:42.961
Took down most of the Iron Sentinels' leadership.

297
00:18:43.043 --> 00:18:44.791
If Belle reactivates that cover.

298
00:18:44.874 --> 00:18:46.415
we've got eyes and ears inside the rally.

299
00:18:46.498 --> 00:18:48.163
Yeah. and when you show up out of the blue.

300
00:18:48.246 --> 00:18:49.411
you're gonna raise suspicions.

301
00:18:49.494 --> 00:18:51.117
Not if she brings something they want.

302
00:18:51.201 --> 00:18:53.365
Still got that meth we took down a few months ago?

303
00:18:53.449 --> 00:18:55.654
Drug dealing is one of the Iron Sentinels'

304
00:18:55.737 --> 00:18:57.485
biggest profit centers.

305
00:18:59.525 --> 00:19:01.523
Okay. what if your contact connects the dots.

306
00:19:01.606 --> 00:19:03.770
thinks you're entrapping him with the drugs?

307
00:19:03.853 --> 00:19:05.476
Mm. based on our history.

308
00:19:05.560 --> 00:19:08.473
he'll have something else on his mind when he sees me.

309
00:19:11.719 --> 00:19:14.133
Okay.

310
00:19:15.382 --> 00:19:18.711
If you can confirm your contact will be there.

311
00:19:18.795 --> 00:19:20.709
I will green-light this op.

312
00:20:01.455 --> 00:20:02.579
Hey. buddy.

313
00:20:13.442 --> 00:20:16.563
I came out here hoping Mom would cheer me up.

314
00:20:17.604 --> 00:20:19.227
She usually does.

315
00:20:27.259 --> 00:20:29.341
Hard to believe it's been a year.

316
00:20:33.294 --> 00:20:35.125
I know how you're feeling.

317
00:20:36.998 --> 00:20:39.995
Losing your mom put a hole in my heart that'll never heal.

318
00:20:41.702 --> 00:20:44.698
I don't need cheering up about the anniversary.

319
00:20:44.781 --> 00:20:46.322
I'm not the one avoiding it.

320
00:20:52.855 --> 00:20:55.394
I just can't stop thinking that Hayley would be safe

321
00:20:55.477 --> 00:20:58.099
if we'd done something when we saw her.

322
00:20:59.598 --> 00:21:01.595
You're not to blame. son.

323
00:21:03.261 --> 00:21:05.466
Fault lies with me.

324
00:21:08.338 --> 00:21:10.794
Mom led us to that truck stop...

325
00:21:12.292 --> 00:21:14.498
...and we didn't deliver.

326
00:21:16.038 --> 00:21:17.911
I disappointed her.

327
00:21:19.367 --> 00:21:21.782
No. that's the last thing you ever did.

328
00:21:24.487 --> 00:21:26.609
You made her whole world bright.

329
00:21:28.940 --> 00:21:31.978
All the more reason to come to the ceremony tomorrow night.

330
00:21:40.344 --> 00:21:43.174
Got to keep my foot on the gas hunting for Hayley.

331
00:21:46.670 --> 00:21:48.917
Rainwater and Mo still here?

332
00:21:51.748 --> 00:21:54.453
I don't want to disappoint Mom tomorrow. too.

333
00:21:56.658 --> 00:21:58.906
Someone's got to honor her memory.

334
00:22:04.858 --> 00:22:07.396
I know you been ducking me after the shenanigans you pulled

335
00:22:07.480 --> 00:22:09.228
at that Iron Sentinel clubhouse.

336
00:22:09.311 --> 00:22:11.017
Shenanigans bear any fruit?

337
00:22:11.101 --> 00:22:13.432
They did. though you might have gone a little overboard

338
00:22:13.514 --> 00:22:17.011
with the. uh. destruction of property and trespassing.

339
00:22:17.094 --> 00:22:19.175
Well. we used to call that "diversion tactics."

340
00:22:19.258 --> 00:22:21.215
Too bad we're not in the sandbox anymore.

341
00:22:21.298 --> 00:22:23.420
What we're fighting for isn't any less important.

342
00:22:23.503 --> 00:22:25.668
Man. I keep warning you. you keep playing outside the lines.

343
00:22:25.751 --> 00:22:27.374
it's gonna cost us our badges.

344
00:22:27.458 --> 00:22:29.705
Are we worried about our badges or finding these girls?

345
00:22:32.243 --> 00:22:33.826
The hell's this?

346
00:22:33.909 --> 00:22:37.072
Prepping to send Belle into the biker rally undercover.

347
00:22:37.155 --> 00:22:38.528
Got 15 kilos here.

348
00:22:38.611 --> 00:22:40.401
Plenty to entice the Iron Sentinels.

349
00:22:40.484 --> 00:22:41.608
Confirmed Squirrel.

350
00:22:41.692 --> 00:22:44.439
my old contact. will be attending the rally.

351
00:22:44.522 --> 00:22:45.687
Let's go.

352
00:22:45.770 --> 00:22:47.976
If you get burned. you're gonna be on your own.

353
00:22:50.223 --> 00:22:52.762
It's not my first rodeo.

354
00:22:52.845 --> 00:22:54.178
Be nice if you could trust me.

355
00:22:54.261 --> 00:22:58.006
I just never like having a teammate downrange alone.

356
00:22:59.047 --> 00:23:00.586
I'm happy to do it for these girls.

357
00:23:00.670 --> 00:23:02.793
And they're as good as gone if we don't try this.

358
00:23:02.876 --> 00:23:04.666
All right. Kayce. Andrea. we're gonna need a mobile HQ

359
00:23:04.749 --> 00:23:07.079
to survey their rally. and Miles.

360
00:23:07.163 --> 00:23:08.786
let's get all the hard armor and rifles.

361
00:23:08.869 --> 00:23:10.118
just in case this thing goes sideways. okay?

362
00:23:10.201 --> 00:23:12.365
Get ready for the ball. Cinderella.

363
00:23:12.448 --> 00:23:13.614
Let's go.

364
00:23:14.738 --> 00:23:15.986
Hey.

365
00:23:21.937 --> 00:23:23.894
What are you gonna tell your husband?

366
00:23:24.934 --> 00:23:28.139
Well. I don't know how that's any of your business.

367
00:23:28.222 --> 00:23:29.346
It's not.

368
00:23:29.429 --> 00:23:32.717
I just imagine how worried he'd be.

369
00:23:36.296 --> 00:23:39.127
I'd tell him he's got nothing to worry about.

370
00:23:40.958 --> 00:23:43.455
I got you watching my back.

371
00:23:57.814 --> 00:23:59.437
It's getting pretty rowdy out there.

372
00:23:59.520 --> 00:24:00.853
Wait till the booze and drugs

373
00:24:00.936 --> 00:24:03.016
kick in after sunset.

374
00:24:04.057 --> 00:24:05.597
Hell of a makeover. girl.

375
00:24:05.680 --> 00:24:08.053
- You ready. Brandi?

376
00:24:08.135 --> 00:24:10.383
Meeting my contact in five.

377
00:24:10.467 --> 00:24:12.215
Okay. We just need you to get eyes on Brimstone.

378
00:24:12.298 --> 00:24:14.171
hope he leads you to the girls.

379
00:24:15.377 --> 00:24:17.292
You won't be able to hear us...

380
00:24:18.873 --> 00:24:21.163
...but this has a mic.

381
00:24:22.994 --> 00:24:24.409
Watch your ass. girl.

382
00:24:44.844 --> 00:24:46.676
Whoo!

383
00:25:00.201 --> 00:25:01.242
This could've been a mistake.

384
00:25:01.325 --> 00:25:02.532
She is catching a lot of looks.

385
00:25:02.615 --> 00:25:03.739
I'd be more worried if a bunch

386
00:25:03.822 --> 00:25:05.195
of horned-up bikers weren't eying her.

387
00:25:05.279 --> 00:25:08.442
Don't see any signs of the girls.

388
00:25:08.525 --> 00:25:10.190
Be ready to roll if you do.

389
00:25:11.230 --> 00:25:13.103
I got eyes on Squirrel.

390
00:25:13.186 --> 00:25:14.893
Okay. here we go.

391
00:25:18.680 --> 00:25:21.136
Well. hello.

392
00:25:22.135 --> 00:25:24.049
Ow!

393
00:25:28.378 --> 00:25:29.876
Whoo!

394
00:25:32.748 --> 00:25:34.205
You got some brass showing up here. Brandi.

395
00:25:34.287 --> 00:25:37.284
Johnny Law showed up right after you ghosted me.

396
00:25:37.368 --> 00:25:38.949
Half our chapter got rolled.

397
00:25:39.032 --> 00:25:40.614
I got pinched. too.

398
00:25:40.697 --> 00:25:44.610
Idaho City with two pounds of crystal.

399
00:25:44.693 --> 00:25:47.357
Mm. Some story.

400
00:25:47.440 --> 00:25:49.271
Oh. yeah?

401
00:25:52.309 --> 00:25:53.433
Two years.

402
00:25:53.516 --> 00:25:55.348
Pocatello.

403
00:25:57.886 --> 00:25:59.218
Oh. that's the thanks I get

404
00:25:59.301 --> 00:26:01.174
for not dropping a dime on you?

405
00:26:01.257 --> 00:26:02.714
Think you can just roll up

406
00:26:02.797 --> 00:26:04.962
and pick things up right where you left them?

407
00:26:05.045 --> 00:26:07.584
I got an old lady now. Remember Charlene?

408
00:26:07.667 --> 00:26:09.582
I'm here on business.

409
00:26:09.665 --> 00:26:10.746
Hmm.

410
00:26:10.830 --> 00:26:12.703
Got fresh product I need to move.

411
00:26:13.868 --> 00:26:15.491
I moved up the ranks.

412
00:26:15.575 --> 00:26:17.031
I don't do small-time deals anymore.

413
00:26:17.114 --> 00:26:18.737
Oh. honey.

414
00:26:19.778 --> 00:26:21.235
Small-time. huh?

415
00:26:21.319 --> 00:26:23.025
That's pure glass.

416
00:26:23.107 --> 00:26:24.980
I've got five here. ten more ready to go.

417
00:26:25.064 --> 00:26:26.271
I'm looking for a partner.

418
00:26:28.311 --> 00:26:30.808
You know anyone who can move this?

419
00:26:33.263 --> 00:26:35.094
I got just the guy. baby.

420
00:26:37.301 --> 00:26:39.131
This guy's top of the food chain around here.

421
00:26:39.214 --> 00:26:40.463
- Uh-huh. - I'll do the talking.

422
00:26:40.547 --> 00:26:42.503
Damn. Belle's pretty smooth.

423
00:26:42.586 --> 00:26:44.542
If the best lies are 90% true.

424
00:26:44.625 --> 00:26:46.498
I got questions for her.

425
00:26:46.581 --> 00:26:48.829
If Brimstone's not the runner she's meeting.

426
00:26:48.912 --> 00:26:50.619
we're gonna have to improvise.

427
00:26:56.320 --> 00:26:58.068
What the hell's this?

428
00:26:58.152 --> 00:27:00.066
Former old lady of mine.

429
00:27:00.150 --> 00:27:02.938
She has a business proposition for you.

430
00:27:11.137 --> 00:27:13.051
- What you got for me? - I don't know.

431
00:27:13.135 --> 00:27:14.924
that depends.

432
00:27:15.008 --> 00:27:16.340
Who the hell are you?

433
00:27:16.422 --> 00:27:18.670
Nomad.

434
00:27:20.502 --> 00:27:23.124
They call me Brimstone. honey.

435
00:27:33.029 --> 00:27:34.777
You weren't kidding.

436
00:27:34.861 --> 00:27:36.192
How much you got?

437
00:27:36.275 --> 00:27:38.315
Fifteen kilos.

438
00:27:38.398 --> 00:27:39.605
bagged...

439
00:27:40.645 --> 00:27:41.769
...and ready.

440
00:27:43.975 --> 00:27:45.515
And you want me to move it for you?

441
00:27:45.599 --> 00:27:47.637
That's right.

442
00:27:47.721 --> 00:27:50.384
I cook. you sell.

443
00:27:51.383 --> 00:27:52.881
That's the deal.

444
00:27:53.880 --> 00:27:55.670
Hmm.

445
00:27:55.753 --> 00:27:59.124
Not so sure we can be partners. since something ain't adding up.

446
00:28:03.703 --> 00:28:05.659
The hell you doing with that skid mark Squirrel?

447
00:28:06.700 --> 00:28:08.406
I don't know.

448
00:28:08.489 --> 00:28:12.152
I guess I always saw it as a stepping stone.

449
00:28:12.235 --> 00:28:14.566
to something...

450
00:28:15.565 --> 00:28:17.188
...bigger.

451
00:28:19.518 --> 00:28:20.725
Better.

452
00:28:24.680 --> 00:28:27.302
Making a run to Calgary tonight with some other product.

453
00:28:27.385 --> 00:28:29.008
Buyer will take yours. too.

454
00:28:30.049 --> 00:28:33.919
Sit tight. I'll be back later to consummate our partnership.

455
00:28:34.002 --> 00:28:35.542
Sounds more like d-drugs than girls.

456
00:28:35.625 --> 00:28:37.748
- What's in Calgary? - A wagon wheel.

457
00:28:37.831 --> 00:28:39.953
If it's illegal in Canada. they run it through there.

458
00:28:40.037 --> 00:28:41.951
Girls make it to the distro center.

459
00:28:42.035 --> 00:28:43.699
they'll be split up and sold out.

460
00:28:43.783 --> 00:28:45.864
And gone for good.

461
00:28:54.187 --> 00:28:56.976
I'm just gonna go pop a squat...

462
00:28:57.059 --> 00:28:59.515
Yeah. I know you.

463
00:29:00.555 --> 00:29:03.011
Your hair's different. but I've seen you before.

464
00:29:04.051 --> 00:29:05.758
Huh.

465
00:29:05.841 --> 00:29:07.340
Was it Sturgis?

466
00:29:08.380 --> 00:29:10.128
No.

467
00:29:10.211 --> 00:29:12.209
- It was Lone Star. - No.

468
00:29:12.292 --> 00:29:14.290
I think it was third base at the blackjack table

469
00:29:14.374 --> 00:29:17.495
at the Laughing Elk a few weeks back.

470
00:29:17.578 --> 00:29:18.910
Mm-hmm.

471
00:29:18.993 --> 00:29:20.866
Your name is Turek or something.

472
00:29:22.989 --> 00:29:24.445
Let's go.

473
00:29:24.528 --> 00:29:26.610
Brimstone wouldn't like you putting your hands

474
00:29:26.693 --> 00:29:29.023
- on his new lady. - Her cover's blown.

475
00:29:29.107 --> 00:29:30.813
Turek? No. he's got her

476
00:29:30.896 --> 00:29:31.979
confused with some other person.

477
00:29:32.062 --> 00:29:34.226
She's gonna sort this out.

478
00:29:34.309 --> 00:29:36.057
We move in. the girls disappear. She's got it.

479
00:29:36.140 --> 00:29:37.264
If this guy jams Belle up.

480
00:29:37.348 --> 00:29:39.346
we're never gonna get eyes on Brimstone.

481
00:29:39.428 --> 00:29:40.635
...off of me.

482
00:29:40.719 --> 00:29:41.843
Yeah?

483
00:29:41.926 --> 00:29:43.965
And the club doesn't take too kindly

484
00:29:44.048 --> 00:29:46.587
to infiltrators. so let's go.

485
00:29:47.586 --> 00:29:49.667
Okay. go. Keep your head down.

486
00:29:57.575 --> 00:29:59.156
Hey. You got any beer?

487
00:30:08.895 --> 00:30:11.600
Where does Brimstone keep his cargo?

488
00:30:20.465 --> 00:30:22.672
- What the hell's going on? - Baby.

489
00:30:22.755 --> 00:30:23.961
he put his hands all over me!

490
00:30:24.045 --> 00:30:26.126
- Son of a bitch. - Ah...

491
00:30:39.361 --> 00:30:41.276
Behind enemy lines now.

492
00:30:41.359 --> 00:30:43.689
And those girls are about to be in the wind.

493
00:30:52.304 --> 00:30:53.762
- Where's Brimstone? - After all that.

494
00:30:53.845 --> 00:30:55.510
you're a pig?

495
00:30:55.593 --> 00:30:57.466
- Wrong answer.

496
00:30:57.549 --> 00:30:59.671
Come on. Squirrel. help us out.

497
00:30:59.755 --> 00:31:01.128
- Go to hell. - You want a life with Charlene.

498
00:31:01.211 --> 00:31:03.126
or you want to spend the rest of your days in jail?

499
00:31:03.209 --> 00:31:07.205
Tell me how Brimstone's moving the girls.

500
00:31:10.576 --> 00:31:12.032
I don't know anything about any girls.

501
00:31:13.365 --> 00:31:14.613
Okay. okay!

502
00:31:14.696 --> 00:31:16.777
He's moving stuff in the box truck out back.

503
00:31:19.316 --> 00:31:21.439
Okay. eyes up for Brimstone's truck.

504
00:31:21.522 --> 00:31:24.186
We're never gonna make it through this.

505
00:31:24.268 --> 00:31:27.015
U.S. Marshals! Clear out!

506
00:31:27.099 --> 00:31:28.306
Let's go!

507
00:31:30.803 --> 00:31:32.843
Eyes on.

508
00:31:34.507 --> 00:31:36.214
They're on the move.

509
00:31:37.795 --> 00:31:40.250
Hey! Brimstone.

510
00:31:41.249 --> 00:31:43.414
I want to renegotiate.

511
00:31:43.497 --> 00:31:46.535
I knew you were gonna be high-maintenance.

512
00:31:46.618 --> 00:31:47.534
Hey! Hey!

513
00:31:47.617 --> 00:31:49.157
Feds are here! The Feds are here!

514
00:31:57.066 --> 00:31:58.689
Cover me.

515
00:31:58.772 --> 00:32:00.187
Move!

516
00:32:40.807 --> 00:32:43.471
Drugs.

517
00:32:48.798 --> 00:32:51.130
We're U.S. Marshals. You're safe.

518
00:32:57.456 --> 00:32:59.578
You did it. You led us here.

519
00:32:59.661 --> 00:33:01.451
The place with the trees.

520
00:33:01.534 --> 00:33:03.532
Yeah.

521
00:33:11.607 --> 00:33:13.230
Thank you.

522
00:33:16.559 --> 00:33:18.889
Chairman Rainwater wanted me to share his thanks.

523
00:33:18.973 --> 00:33:22.053
Girls are all recovering in the IHS hospital.

524
00:33:22.136 --> 00:33:24.258
Reunited with their families.

525
00:33:24.342 --> 00:33:26.256
Appreciate you taking on this fight.

526
00:33:26.340 --> 00:33:27.754
That's what this team was stood up for.

527
00:33:27.838 --> 00:33:28.962
Causes like this.

528
00:33:29.045 --> 00:33:30.710
We do this job because others can't.

529
00:33:33.914 --> 00:33:36.828
We wouldn't have done it without our very own Mata Hari here.

530
00:33:36.911 --> 00:33:39.616
Well. it got a little dicier than I had hoped.

531
00:33:39.700 --> 00:33:41.239
Hey. what was that guy going on about.

532
00:33:41.323 --> 00:33:43.279
seeing you at the casino?

533
00:33:44.361 --> 00:33:45.484
Who knows?

534
00:33:45.568 --> 00:33:48.273
That guy was hyped up on something.

535
00:33:48.356 --> 00:33:49.689
Yeah. he was.

536
00:33:49.772 --> 00:33:52.352
I buy you more as a biker babe than a card shark.

537
00:33:52.436 --> 00:33:54.724
Must be ready to shed this persona.

538
00:33:55.723 --> 00:33:57.096
Right?

539
00:33:57.180 --> 00:33:59.178
Back to reality.

540
00:34:04.963 --> 00:34:06.086
Maddie?

541
00:34:10.331 --> 00:34:11.664
I'm better at finding missing girls

542
00:34:11.747 --> 00:34:13.745
than I am reconnecting with my own.

543
00:34:17.366 --> 00:34:19.530
Look. if you want. I will be your wingman tonight.

544
00:34:19.613 --> 00:34:21.486
We can go to the bar...

545
00:34:22.485 --> 00:34:24.400
...just force the issue on her.

546
00:34:28.062 --> 00:34:30.393
Think I'm gonna savor the victory

547
00:34:30.476 --> 00:34:34.679
rather than face another defeat with Maddie.

548
00:34:36.261 --> 00:34:37.385
Yeah.

549
00:34:39.383 --> 00:34:41.214
Now that we found the girls...

550
00:34:42.255 --> 00:34:44.335
...figured I'd share this with you.

551
00:34:44.418 --> 00:34:46.541
The building across from mine has a unit available.

552
00:34:46.625 --> 00:34:48.538
If you're looking to leave Broken Rock.

553
00:34:48.622 --> 00:34:50.037
you could do a lot worse.

554
00:34:51.410 --> 00:34:53.575
Right. Thanks.

555
00:35:21.918 --> 00:35:23.042
Don't get mad.

556
00:35:23.125 --> 00:35:25.122
I'm keeping my distance this time.

557
00:35:26.787 --> 00:35:29.077
Maneater sure is beautiful.

558
00:35:30.117 --> 00:35:32.156
Perfect for your mother.

559
00:35:33.862 --> 00:35:36.444
You seem weirdly happy today.

560
00:35:36.526 --> 00:35:37.942
That mean you're making progress with Hayley?

561
00:35:41.563 --> 00:35:43.186
We got her back. son.

562
00:35:45.184 --> 00:35:47.847
All ten girls have been reunited with their families.

563
00:35:56.129 --> 00:35:58.544
And you found your own way to honor Mom.

564
00:37:14.708 --> 00:37:16.622
It's weird seeing you back on the rez.

565
00:37:18.661 --> 00:37:20.659
I'm just glad you decided to do this.

566
00:37:21.658 --> 00:37:23.406
I'm here to support you. son.

567
00:37:26.111 --> 00:37:29.108
I just wish I'd found Mom's necklace.

568
00:37:29.192 --> 00:37:31.064
But I guess I'd rather have you here.

569
00:37:33.145 --> 00:37:34.810
Lala!

570
00:37:39.638 --> 00:37:41.469
Good to see you.

571
00:37:41.553 --> 00:37:43.716
Now here's a ghost I didn't think we'd see here today.

572
00:37:46.089 --> 00:37:50.209
Losing Monica was painful enough.

573
00:37:50.293 --> 00:37:53.872
Your presence makes me feel like...

574
00:37:55.412 --> 00:37:57.742
...I haven't lost another son. too.

575
00:37:59.074 --> 00:38:00.906
Afraid you're stuck with me. sir.

576
00:38:03.611 --> 00:38:05.192
Thank you.

577
00:38:06.857 --> 00:38:08.356
Thank you. son.

578
00:38:12.059 --> 00:38:14.182
Come on. grandson. let's go.

579
00:38:21.216 --> 00:38:23.546
This is a surprise.

580
00:38:24.587 --> 00:38:27.084
Day's been full of them. Good ones.

581
00:38:28.125 --> 00:38:30.997
Finding Hayley and those girls was the cure we all needed.

582
00:38:32.037 --> 00:38:34.159
Yeah. I once told Monica

583
00:38:34.243 --> 00:38:37.864
that she made a difference because she risked everything.

584
00:38:38.904 --> 00:38:40.861
Perhaps she learned that from you.

585
00:38:42.859 --> 00:38:45.564
It's an honor. to remember the ones we've loved.

586
00:38:53.887 --> 00:38:55.428
If we can bleed together.

587
00:38:55.510 --> 00:38:57.342
well. we can grieve together.

588
00:38:57.425 --> 00:38:59.506
I appreciate y'all coming.

589
00:38:59.590 --> 00:39:02.794
Are you gonna stand? For Monica?

590
00:39:02.877 --> 00:39:05.084
No. I'm-a leave that to Tate and his grandpa.

591
00:39:06.415 --> 00:39:07.539
Thank you. Miles.

592
00:39:10.036 --> 00:39:11.576
We're so glad you're here.

593
00:39:12.825 --> 00:39:15.363
We're proud of you. Miles.

594
00:39:15.447 --> 00:39:17.403
Doesn't look like anyone's gonna evict you after all.

595
00:39:18.818 --> 00:39:20.233
I'm not going anywhere.

596
00:39:28.099 --> 00:39:29.306
Excuse us.

597
00:39:38.962 --> 00:39:40.169
Auntie.

598
00:39:42.417 --> 00:39:44.372
I'm sorry I let you and Ava down.

599
00:39:44.455 --> 00:39:45.871
Stop it. Miles.

600
00:39:47.868 --> 00:39:52.197
Thanks to you. I can finally begin to grieve.

601
00:40:05.391 --> 00:40:08.138
Welcome. to all.

602
00:40:08.221 --> 00:40:10.343
This is our way

603
00:40:10.426 --> 00:40:12.549
of acknowledging the spirits

604
00:40:12.633 --> 00:40:15.130
of our Broken Rock family

605
00:40:15.213 --> 00:40:18.334
who departed over the past year.

606
00:40:18.417 --> 00:40:21.123
Here. they will be readied

607
00:40:21.206 --> 00:40:23.786
and safeguarded for their journey.

608
00:40:25.326 --> 00:40:27.324
Will the families come forward?

609
00:41:16.685 --> 00:41:18.142
You found it?

610
00:41:19.141 --> 00:41:21.430
Been clinging to it since Mom left us.

611
00:41:22.679 --> 00:41:25.134
Maybe it's time I start letting go.

611
00:41:26.305 --> 00:42:26.592
